{
  "texts": [
    "Academic discourse has thus far only provided piecemeal or theoretical perspectives on the DSA's potential [61,78,82,104,108,109,169], rather than rigorously quantifying its multidimensional effects on complex factors enabling the phenomenon of disinformation.",
    "Potentially, this could be because it was premature to position the DSA's direct contribution to curbing online mis/disinformation.",
    "1 However, without comprehensive, empirical evaluation, the DSA's suitability for effective AI governance remains speculative.",
    "This is why the present research argues for the necessity of gathering robust evidence on the efficacy of DSA mechanisms through a range of quantitative and qualitative methods.",
    "This translates to the overarching research question: How can comprehensive, empirical research effectively quantify and evaluate the real-world impacts of the DSA's mechanisms on combating online disinformation?Bridging this gap requires a three-pronged approach."
  ]
}